%N A372482 a(n) is the numerator of the probability that the procedure described in A372422 successfully ends with the selection of a single person, starting with n persons.
%C A372482 See A372422 for more information.
%C A372482 The probability is somewhat similar to that for a single survivor as in "group Russian roulette" of A372480. However, the mean of the periodic change is higher (approximately 0.721347 instead of 0.4814...), the amplitude is much smaller, and the period is ~log2(n) instead of ~log(n).
